"I am a Software Engineer with a Master’s degree from Wroclaw University of Science and Technology (2017) that specializes in full-stack development with .NET, focusing on creating user-centric software. My experience includes AWS infrastructure, CI/CD pipelines, and process automation. I thrive in collaborative environments and am dedicated to continuous learning and problem-solving."

"As a key member of the team, I contributed to the development and maintenance of a product used by Big Pharma companies for tracking, storing, and managing samples. My responsibilities included implementing new features with high code quality standards, supporting customers, and contributing to documentation."
"Implemented new features using the .NET stack, ensuring high code quality standards and adherence to best practices in software development"
"Supported customers and contributed to comprehensive documentation."
"Developed AWS-based infrastructure for rapid deployment of testing and development environments."
"Created Docker-based images to enhance developer efficiency."
"Built a fully functional, interactive dashboard featured in the company’s marketing materials."
"Collaborated closely with both manual and automated testers to ensure thorough testing of features."
"Mentored newcomers and provided guidance on best practices."
"Performed application testing to verify functionality and quality according to specifications."

"This project required extensive cross-team communication between the Polish and British office branches. I primarily focused on developing the API side of the module, ensuring robust and efficient backend functionality. Additionally, I played a significant role in the frontend development, working closely with colleagues to create an interactive and user-friendly interface. The project was highly requested by customers as it aimed to retire the older version, providing enhanced features and improved user experience. I also developed automated UI tests using Selenium to ensure the reliability and quality of the user interface."
"Implemented APIs using C# with a functional programming approach, contributing to shared code modules within the monolithic application"
"Developed unit tests using the MSTest framework to ensure code reliability and functionality"
"Developed automated UI tests using the Selenium framework and mentored aspiring UI testers on best practices"
"Utilized React and TypeScript as primary technologies to implement features based on provided mockups and design specifications"

"Developed a system synchronization tool to ensure seamless integration and functionality across different, not always compatible versions of the same product. I led the development efforts, guiding colleagues and mentoring an intern throughout the process. The project involved synchronizing data between complex database systems without relying on entity IDs, while preserving entity relationships. Extensive validation was performed, and any issues were reported to users with changes rolled back as necessary"
"Designing a transient JSON file system for storing and editing entity information before final data entry"
"Emphasizing high code quality, coverage and utilizing a functional programming approach"

"This project enabled the quick creation of working cloud installations for demo and testing purposes. The goal was to allow anyone to request an instance, use it for development or testing, and then tear down the application. I was involved in developing Docker-based images for local deployments and contributed to the initial phases of moving the deployment process onto AWS. Additionally, I provided ongoing support for internal teams with both Docker-related issues and AWS system use. An additional supporting web application was created to ease the management of environments, to which I contributed significantly."
"Involved in moving the deployment process onto AWS"
"Provided support for internal teams with Docker and AWS issues"
"Contributed to creating a supporting web application for environment management"

"Worked on a fulfilment module application that required constant updates due to frequent client requests for new features. This project involved a variety of tasks to enhance the module’s functionality and maintain its performance."
"Implemented strategies to reduce the number of output labware needed for fulfilment, optimizing resource usage and efficiency"
"Developed a tool to assist the support team with common maintenance tasks, making their work more efficient and reducing downtime"
"Conducted performance testing identifying and addressing potential bottlenecks"
"Added a mechanism to automatically clean up old runs."
"Created scripts to streamline the deployment process, making it easier to set up the application in different environments"
"Provided detailed guidance to tester teams about the module’s internals, helping them understand the system better and perform more effective testing"
"Actively supported customers by addressing their issues and incorporating their feedback into the application, ensuring a user-friendly experience"
"Company's first UI and UX-oriented product. This dashboard, built with C# and Knockout.js, was well-received by customers for its user-friendly design and functionality."
"Guided the project from start to finish, ensuring it met business and user requirements"
"Developed interface with primary focus on the users."
"Created detailed mockups and implemented the frontend using Knockout.js"
"Designed and developed robust APIs to support the dashboard’s functionality"
"Delivered a product that garnered positive feedback for its usability"
"Internal core module migration from VB6 to C#"

"Worked on migrating complicated core module from VB6 to C#. Project involved refactoring legacy code to increase performance and maintainability. The module is directly used by most of the fulfilment modules (including the JFM)."
